The paper discusses the acceleration of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) on Field Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGAs) using OpenCL, which falls under the category of Computer Architecture and Embedded Systems (cs.AR). The paper also focuses on the performance of ANNs on image datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10, which suggests Computer Vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of regularization techniques to binarize network weights, which is a common technique in Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the power consumption and efficiency of the FPGA-accelerated networks, which could also fall under the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET).
